{"serial": "07006", "department_serial": 5, "code": "CC0145", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Literary Masterpieces(Narrative and Thinking)", "ch": "人文經典-敘事與思想"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Yi, Peng"], "ch": ["易鵬"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 1, "session": ["3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "C2", "room": "101"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 76, "department": {"ch": "總教學中心", "en": "Teaching Center"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 37, "selected": 56, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "此課程整體設計將分成三個層次：（一）思想與敘事之間密切關連，（二）敘事如何開發出本身的想像空間使思想能夠擴展其可能性，（三）如何看到實際思想與敘事相互創發的實例。", "en": "The course will explore three interconnected strands: first the course tries to deal with the ways in which narrative enables thinking. Second, it deals with the ways in which narrative create an altenative space in which thinking can erect new edifice and finally the course attempts to find examples how narrative and thinking can help each other to go in new directions."}, "outline": {"ch": "這個主體思想與敘事活動相互創發的實例之一即是以同名科幻小說改編的《接觸未來》（“Contact“ 1997, dir. Robert Zemeckis）。此影片主要描述離經叛道女科學家Eleanor Arroway (Ellie)生平志願在於尋找外星生命訊息。經過許多挫折，她因為另一位亦是才華縱橫但也離經叛道的神秘企業家支持，終於與來自外太空，織女星座（Vega）的智慧生物訊息，建立聯繫。同時，她亦與一位宗教人士Palmer Joss認識，並且兩人心儀。外星訊息事實上包括有關一座神秘載具建造指示。影片在科學理性、Joss在Ellie身上所展開宗教的議題，政治角力，以及如何說服以及描述給世人，只有Ellie一個人經驗到的時空之旅等主題中展開。\n本課程將以此影片以及《異星入境》作為貫穿整個課程主線。藉由此一影片，我希望一方面能夠使得學生能夠有一個較明確的討論焦點與參考點，同時經由影片所發展出的一系列與課程主要議題－敘事與思想－相關的重點，使得學生可以針對這些重點，產生其本身對影片以及授課內容不同的詮釋。", "en": "During the course of the semester, we will try to read, view and discuss literary works, movies related to or adapted from the works, and other related materials. In additon to literary works, we will also deal with movies such as “Contact“ and “The Arrival“ (《異星入境》(adapted from Ted Chiang‘s “The Story of Your Life“)."}, "textbook": {"ch": "閱讀材料將於開學前上傳至ee-class系統。其他相關課程材料亦會適時陸續開放使用或觀看。", "en": "A compliation of the reading materials will be uploaded to the ee-class system before the beginning of the semester. Other relevant materials will be made available in due course."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100%", "en": "100%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "出席與課堂表現30％，口頭報告30％，學期作業40％", "en": "attendance and in-class performance, 30％; in-class oral presentations, 30％; final assignment 40％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期一, 0900-0950; 星期二, 1000-1150", "en": "Monday, 0900-0950; Tuesday, 1000-1150"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "17週：課程材料回顧複習以及準備期末作業，\n18週：期末作業之提案以及實施。", "en": "The 17th Week, time will be devoted to course material review and preparation for the end-of-term assignment and the 18th Week, we will conduct the discussion of the final assignment proposal and the drafting."}, "domain": {"ch": "人文與思想領域", "en": "人文與思想領域"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "邏輯與創新", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "多元與溝通", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "美感與鑑賞", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "關懷與實踐", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Assignments", "Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["學制:限學士班。"], "en": ["Type:Undergraduate Program only."]}, "preselecStu": 56, "stuGender": {"male": 26, "Female": 30}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "maste